  "datePublished": "2026-03-01",
  "description": "A controlled vocabulary is a curated, maintained list of terms used for labeling, indexing, and categorizing content within a collection. Its purpose is consistency: ensuring that the same concept is always referred to by the same term, and that different concepts are not accidentally given the same label.",
